<h3>Sublime Text</h3>
<p>
	<b>site:</b> <a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/">https://www.sublimetext.com/</a>
</p>

<p>
I have found sublime to be a particularly useful text editor, primarily because:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		it handles really large files speedily and can collapse all code blocks of a given depth easily; 
	</li>
	<li>
		packages can easily be modified, and you can put pull requests in to the package mantainers to have those changes added; and
	</li>
	<li>
		It has sufficiently decent syntax highlighting and auto completion, even for my own languages in-built in to <a href="https://nift.dev">Nift</a>.
	</li>
</ul>

